column1: #Text=( Irish : Contae Chill Dara ) is in Ireland ' s East Coast and Midlands .
#Text=It is south of Dublin and also borders County Wicklow and County Laois as well as County Meath .
#Text=( Nás na Ríogh , " Meeting Place of the Kings " ) – county town
#Text=( Baile Átha Í , " town of the ford of Ae " )
#Text=( Cill Dara , " church of the oak " )
#Text=Kildare is known as " the shortgrass county " , revealing its fame for sheep farming in the plains to the south .
#Text=It is the horsebreeding capital of Ireland and home to the Curragh Racecourse , as well as many studfarms .
#Text=Historically , it was inside the Anglised area known as " The Pale " and ruled by landlords such as the Fitzgeralds .
#Text=County Kildare is Ireland 's wealthiest county outside Dublin with many middle and upper class residents mainly in the north east of the county eg Naas and Maynooth .
#Text=The largest town is Naas with a population of 30,000 and is also is the county town .
#Text=( Outside Kildare Town located adjacent to The Japanese Gardens ) .
#Text=This is a working thoroughbred horse farm .
#Text=The Curragh is home to the five Irish Classic Horse Races .
#Text=Punchestown , near Naas is a steeplechase race track and home to the four day Punchestown Festival in late April .
#Text=, Castletown House , Celbridge , Co. Kildare , W23 V9H3 ( From the M4 take Exit 6 ( Celbridge West/Leixlip West Exit - R449 , signposted for Castletown and Hewlett Packard ) .

#Text=There are some excellent golf courses in Kildare : The K Club ( which hosted the 2006 Ryder Cup ) , Carton House , and Castlewarden Glof Clubs .
